  "title": "DCIM System Specialist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Summary:</strong><br />We are seeking a <strong>DCIM System Specialist</strong> with strong knowledge of data center operations and hands-on experience (or familiarity) with DCIM platforms. The role involves configuring fault alerts, incident workflows, and ticketing systems, with a focus on power and cooling chain–based fault logic.</p><p>The successful candidate will translate data center operational knowledge into actionable rules and workflows within a DCIM system. Training on the DCIM software will be provided.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Understand and apply end-to-end data center operational workflows, including power and cooling chain dependencies.</p></li><li><p>Interpret Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), Maintenance Operating Procedures (MOPs), Emergency Operating Procedures (EOPs), and escalation processes.</p></li><li><p>Define and configure fault alerts based on power and cooling chain topology.</p></li><li><p>Configure incident workflows and ticketing within the DCIM system.</p></li><li><p>Maintain and update DCIM software configurations, including asset topology, fault rules, and workflows.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with DCIM software vendors and data center operations teams to ensure alignment between system configuration and operational reality.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Required Skills and Experience:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Strong knowledge of data center operations, facilities management, or critical infrastructure.</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience configuring DCIM software (commercial experience is a plus).</p></li><li><p>Good understanding of Building Management Systems (BMS), Integrated BMS (IBMS), and Energy Management Systems (EMS).</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with project management principles.</p></li><li><p>Strong analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Training:</strong></p><ul><li><p>On-the-job training for the specific DCIM software will be provided.</p></li></ul>",
